intro: Warea cuneifolia, commonly known as the narrow-leaf warea, is a flowering plant native to eastern Australia. It belongs to the family Orchidaceae, commonly known as the orchid family. The plant is characterized by its slender, grass-like leaves and produces delicate, greenish-white flowers. It typically grows in shaded, moist environments such as rainforests and understoreys. Warea cuneifolia is often found in coastal and inland regions, thriving in humid, temperate climates.
